      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The FE model uses a nonlinear elastic (Ogden hyperelastic) constitutive model for UHMWPE, which is appropriate for the strain magnitudes encountered (< 5% in the contact region). Model form selection is justified by published literature comparing linear elastic, bilinear elastic-plastic, and hyperelastic representations of UHMWPE contact stress; hyperelastic model reduces systematic error vs. linear elastic by 18% relative to experimental measurements. Model form uncertainty assessed through comparison of three constitutive formulations; hyperelastic selected as best-performing with documented justification.",
